Uploading a CloudFileItem to a CloudSyncbox

 Adding content to a CloudSyncbox can be done by uploading multiple files or a single file.


* Add a single file.

+---+
cloudSyncbox
	.addFile(fileToUpload.getAbsolutePath(), toPath)
	.handle(new CloudCallHandler<CloudFileItem>() {

		@Override
		public void onError(Exception error) {
			//Cloud not upload file
		}

		@Override
		public void onSuccess(CloudFileItem cloudFileItem) throws Exception {
			//use uploaded file
		}
	});
+---+

* Adding multiple files
 
+---+

cloudSyncbox
	.addFiles(Arrays.asList(pathOfFile1,pathOfFile2,pathOfFile3), currentFileFolder.path())
	.handle(new CloudCallHandler<List<CloudFileItem>>() {
		
		@Override
		public void onError(Exception error) {
			//Could not upload files	
		}
		
		@Override
		public void onSuccess(List<CloudFileItem> cloudFileItems)
				throws Exception {
			//use uploaded files
		}
	});
+---+